# _sys/boot scope 100 — EXECUTE the route decided at scope 0.
#
# The route-or-not decision is THIS visible WHEN, not hidden in Go:
# only fire when scope 0 (or an intervening hook) left a route
# proposal. An unrouted request has no _txc.route.to, skips this rule,
# and falls through to the scope 1000 404.
#
# txco://route is pure mechanism — it promotes the inert _txc.route.*
# proposal into the active _txc.goto (+ _txc.tenant and parity keys),
# which triggers the one-way _sys->tenant re-tenant gate and the jump
# into the resolved tenant's stack. It lives in Go only because txcl
# SET can assign literals, not copy one envelope path to another.
#
# @ is sugar for ._txc.
WHEN @route.to != ""
  EXEC "txco://route"
